@page "/privacy"
@layout PublicLayout

<PageTitle>Privacy Policy - grow.IT</PageTitle>

<div class="contact-page footer-info-page">
    <section class="contact-hero">
        <span class="contact-kicker">Privacy</span>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p>Last updated: July 4, 2026. This page explains how Grow.IT handles account, organization, service, reporting, and platform data.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-form-section">
        <article class="contact-form-card">
            <h2>Data we collect</h2>
            <p>We collect account details, organization setup information, team and role information, people and household records, programs, funds, service records, documents, outcomes, follow-ups, reports, support messages, and system activity needed to operate the platform.</p>

            <h2>How we use data</h2>
            <p>We use data to provide the product, secure accounts, support reporting, calculate readiness signals, help teams reuse saved information, troubleshoot issues, and improve platform quality.</p>

            <h2>Data sharing</h2>
            <p>We do not sell personal data. We may use trusted infrastructure, email, hosting, analytics, payment, and support providers strictly to operate Grow.IT and serve customer organizations.</p>

            <h2>Data ownership and export</h2>
            <p>Customer organizations retain ownership of the operational data they enter. Grow.IT is designed so information can be reused in reports, spreadsheets, documents, and future integrations instead of being trapped in the platform.</p>

            <h2>Retention and deletion</h2>
            <p>We retain data as needed to provide services, meet legal obligations, protect security, and support customer records. Eligible access, correction, export, or deletion requests can be submitted through the contact page.</p>
        </article>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-cta">
        <div class="contact-cta-card">
            <h2>Questions about data handling?</h2>
            <p>Contact us for privacy, retention, or export questions.</p>
            <div class="contact-cta-actions">
                <a href="/contact?subject=Privacy%20Question" class="btn btn-primary">Contact Us</a>
                <a href="/security" class="btn btn-outline">View Security</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
